00080 /* wrapper for poll callback */
00081 static int RKS_POLL_rna_internal(KeyingSetInfo *ksi, bContext *C)
00082 {
00083     extern FunctionRNA rna_KeyingSetInfo_poll_func;
00084 
00085     PointerRNA ptr;
00086     ParameterList list;
00087     FunctionRNA *func;
00088     void *ret;
00089     int ok;
00090 
00091     RNA_pointer_create(NULL, ksi->ext.srna, ksi, &ptr);
00092     func = &rna_KeyingSetInfo_poll_func; /* RNA_struct_find_function(&ptr, "poll"); */
00093 
00094     RNA_parameter_list_create(&list, &ptr, func);
00095         /* hook up arguments */
00096         RNA_parameter_set_lookup(&list, "ksi", &ksi);
00097         RNA_parameter_set_lookup(&list, "context", &C);
00098         
00099         /* execute the function */
00100         ksi->ext.call(C, &ptr, func, &list);
00101         
00102         /* read the result */
00103         RNA_parameter_get_lookup(&list, "ok", &ret);
00104         ok = *(int*)ret;
00105     RNA_parameter_list_free(&list);
00106     
00107     return ok;
00108 }

00166 static void rna_KeyingSetInfo_unregister(Main *bmain, StructRNA *type)
00167 {
00168     KeyingSetInfo *ksi = RNA_struct_blender_type_get(type);
00169 
00170     if (ksi == NULL)
00171         return;
00172     
00173     /* free RNA data referencing this */
00174     RNA_struct_free_extension(type, &ksi->ext);
00175     RNA_struct_free(&BLENDER_RNA, type);
00176     
00177     /* unlink Blender-side data */
00178     ANIM_keyingset_info_unregister(bmain, ksi);
00179 }
00180 
00181 static StructRNA *rna_KeyingSetInfo_register(Main *bmain, ReportList *reports, void *data, const char *identifier,
00182                                              StructValidateFunc validate, StructCallbackFunc call, StructFreeFunc free)
00183 {
00184     KeyingSetInfo dummyksi = {NULL};
00185     KeyingSetInfo *ksi;
00186     PointerRNA dummyptr = {{NULL}};
00187     int have_function[3];
00188 
00189     /* setup dummy type info to store static properties in */
00190     /* TODO: perhaps we want to get users to register as if they're using 'KeyingSet' directly instead? */
00191     RNA_pointer_create(NULL, &RNA_KeyingSetInfo, &dummyksi, &dummyptr);
00192     
00193     /* validate the python class */
00194     if (validate(&dummyptr, data, have_function) != 0)
00195         return NULL;
00196     
00197     if (strlen(identifier) >= sizeof(dummyksi.idname)) {
00198         BKE_reportf(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Registering keying set info class: '%s' is too long, maximum length is %d",
00199                     identifier, (int)sizeof(dummyksi.idname));
00200         return NULL;
00201     }
00202     
00203     /* check if we have registered this info before, and remove it */
00204     ksi = ANIM_keyingset_info_find_named(dummyksi.idname);
00205     if (ksi && ksi->ext.srna)
00206         rna_KeyingSetInfo_unregister(bmain, ksi->ext.srna);
00207     
00208     /* create a new KeyingSetInfo type */
00209     ksi = MEM_callocN(sizeof(KeyingSetInfo), "python keying set info");
00210     memcpy(ksi, &dummyksi, sizeof(KeyingSetInfo));
00211     
00212     /* set RNA-extensions info */
00213     ksi->ext.srna = RNA_def_struct(&BLENDER_RNA, ksi->idname, "KeyingSetInfo");
00214     ksi->ext.data = data;
00215     ksi->ext.call = call;
00216     ksi->ext.free = free;
00217     RNA_struct_blender_type_set(ksi->ext.srna, ksi);
00218     
00219     /* set callbacks */
00220     /* NOTE: we really should have all of these...  */
00221     ksi->poll = (have_function[0])? RKS_POLL_rna_internal: NULL;
00222     ksi->iter = (have_function[1])? RKS_ITER_rna_internal: NULL;
00223     ksi->generate = (have_function[2])? RKS_GEN_rna_internal: NULL;
00224     
00225     /* add and register with other info as needed */
00226     ANIM_keyingset_info_register(ksi);
00227     
00228     /* return the struct-rna added */
00229     return ksi->ext.srna;
00230 }

00346 static KS_Path *rna_KeyingSet_paths_add(KeyingSet *keyingset, ReportList *reports,
00347         ID *id, const char rna_path[], int index, int group_method, const char group_name[])
00348 {
00349     KS_Path *ksp = NULL;
00350     short flag = 0;
00351     
00352     /* special case when index = -1, we key the whole array (as with other places where index is used) */
00353     if (index == -1) {
00354         flag |= KSP_FLAG_WHOLE_ARRAY;
00355         index = 0;
00356     }
00357     
00358     /* if data is valid, call the API function for this */
00359     if (keyingset) {
00360         ksp = BKE_keyingset_add_path(keyingset, id, group_name, rna_path, index, flag, group_method);
00361         keyingset->active_path = BLI_countlist(&keyingset->paths);
00362     }
00363     else {
00364         BKE_report(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Keying Set Path could not be added");
00365     }
00366     
00367     /* return added path */
00368     return ksp;
00369 }
00370 
00371 static void rna_KeyingSet_paths_remove(KeyingSet *keyingset, ReportList *reports, KS_Path *ksp)
00372 {
00373     /* if data is valid, call the API function for this */
00374     if (keyingset && ksp) {
00375         /* remove the active path from the KeyingSet */
00376         BKE_keyingset_free_path(keyingset, ksp);
00377             
00378         /* the active path number will most likely have changed */
00379         /* TODO: we should get more fancy and actually check if it was removed, but this will do for now */
00380         keyingset->active_path = 0;
00381     }
00382     else {
00383         BKE_report(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Keying Set Path could not be removed");
00384     }
00385 }
00386 
00387 static void rna_KeyingSet_paths_clear(KeyingSet *keyingset, ReportList *reports)
00388 {
00389     /* if data is valid, call the API function for this */
00390     if (keyingset) {
00391         KS_Path *ksp, *kspn;
00392         
00393         /* free each path as we go to avoid looping twice */
00394         for (ksp = keyingset->paths.first; ksp; ksp = kspn) {
00395             kspn = ksp->next;
00396             BKE_keyingset_free_path(keyingset, ksp);
00397         }
00398             
00399         /* reset the active path, since there aren't any left */
00400         keyingset->active_path = 0;
00401     }
00402     else {
00403         BKE_report(reports, RPT_ERROR, "Keying Set Paths could not be removed");
00404     }
00405 }

00439 static FCurve *rna_Driver_from_existing(AnimData *adt, bContext *C, FCurve *src_driver)
00440 {
00441     /* verify that we've got a driver to duplicate */
00442     if (ELEM(NULL, src_driver, src_driver->driver)) {
00443         BKE_reportf(CTX_wm_reports(C), RPT_ERROR, "No valid driver data to create copy of");
00444         return NULL;
00445     }
00446     else {
00447         /* just make a copy of the existing one and add to self */
00448         FCurve *new_fcu = copy_fcurve(src_driver);
00449         
00450         /* XXX: if we impose any ordering on these someday, this will be problematic */
00451         BLI_addtail(&adt->drivers, new_fcu);
00452         return new_fcu;
00453     }
00454 }
